# Context-Aware Data Collection (Mandatory)

Status: **ENTERPRISE APPROVED** · Platform-wide UX design principle for Catalyst One v1.0.

## Principle

Catalyst One must **never ask users for irrelevant information**.

Every screen, form, calculator, wizard, and workspace must dynamically adapt based on the selected **Customer Category** (or equivalent Employment Type).

The user should feel that Catalyst One understands the customer before asking questions.

## Families

| Family | Includes | Show | Hide |
|--------|----------|------|------|
| **Salaried** | Salaried, NRI (salary-path) | Salary, Employer, Employment Type, Salary Credits, Existing EMIs, CIBIL, Property (when applicable) | Business Turnover, GST, ITR Business Income, Gross Margin, Banking Surrogate, Balance Sheet, P&L, Business Vintage, CMA, Business Banking, SE-only fields |
| **Self-employed** | Self-Employed Professional, Self-Employed Business | Business Turnover, Vintage, GST, ITR, Banking, Profit, Balance Sheet, Rental Income, Existing EMIs, CIBIL | Employer Name, Salary, Salary Credits, Employer Type, salaried-only fields |

Shared (always when relevant): Existing EMIs, CIBIL, Product, Amount, Property (product-gated).

## Behaviour rules

1. Changing Customer Category **immediately** updates visible fields.
2. Irrelevant fields **disappear** (do not merely disable).
3. Previously entered irrelevant values **must not influence calculations** — sanitize / exclude on category change and before any compute.
4. Prefer **Context-Aware Forms** via `src/lib/context-aware-data-collection` — do not invent per-screen gating vocabularies.
5. Align category IDs with ECM employment types (`salaried`, `self-employed-professional`, `self-employed-business`).

## Applies to

Contact Creation · Opportunity Workspace · Analyze Deal · Loan File · Customer Profile · Financial Profile · Calculators · COMPASS Customer Journey · all future modules.

## Source of truth

- Types: `src/types/context-aware-data-collection.ts`
- Constants: `src/constants/context-aware-data-collection`
- Lib: `src/lib/context-aware-data-collection`
- Contact role templates remain complementary for ECM MIR fields (`isEcmFieldRelevant`)
